        <section id="Manjara Dam" class="section">
            <h2>Manjara Dam</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Manjara Dam" class="section-image">
            <p>The Manjara Dam, an earthfill dam on the Manjara River in Maharashtra, India, is a vital water resource for Latur and other nearby districts. The dam also plays a role in irrigation, flood control, and power generation. In recent years, the dam has experienced significant fluctuations in water levels, even drying up completely in September 2016 after four years of drought. However, thanks to subsequent rainfall, the reservoir became full again by the end of that same month.Efforts to address the water crisis in the Latur region included river rejuvenation projects, although these have faced criticism regarding their effectiveness and environmental impact. Studies conducted on the backwater of Manjara Dam in Dhanegaon suggested the water was unsuitable for human consumption without treatment.</p>
            <p></p>
